Legal Calculus 4.5 — Enhanced Modules — Module 32
📘 Legal Calculus — Module 32

The Public Case Page — Notion/GitHub Playbook

⚖️ Core Message

A live case page turns complexity into a single, transparent link.
📖 Lesson Content

1. Landing Sections: Case overview, timeline, filings, exhibits, media, contact.
2. Linking: One URL per asset; short labels (Date • Title • Hash).
3. Access: Public read‑only; private workspace for drafts and notes.
4. Cadence: Update within 24 hours; add a 'What changed?' line.
📝 Assignment

Create a one‑page outline for your case page with headings and bullet links (use placeholder URLs and hashes).
✅ Model Response

CASE PAGE (outline)

• Overview — one paragraph 'what/why now'

• Timeline — 10 dated bullets with links

• Filings — Dkt# • Title • SHA256 • Link

• Exhibits — Ex label • Bates • Link

 

💡 Reflection Summary

One link beats twenty attachments.
🎨 Visual Concept

A single URL icon branching to timeline, filings, and exhibits.
